CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, November 1, 1938, pg. 11, reads: "Throughout the county the Young Men's Christian Association is launching drives to increase the membership of their association. In Pittsburg, [sic] PA., the group, left, Samuel Scott, Atty. Theron Hamilton and Dr. King, were the winning team in campaign drive.  They called themselves "The Eagles..."
TitMainTitle: Samuel "Scotty" Scott, Theron Hamilton, and Dr. King holding 1938 YMCA membership campaign banner, in Centre Avenue YMCA
